The Library of Yi Literature of China's Southwest Minzu University has a collection of more than 6,000 books and documents. It is a platform for learning and researching Yi literature. Mosecihuo, a teacher of the Yi ethnic group at Southwest Minzu University, introduces some old bookbinding forms of Yi books. Video director: Ding Qian Videographer: Ma Lei Video editor: Liu Haibo (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)